  "text": "For the PIV measurement typically the interrogation window size dictates the spatial resolution. However, PIV is usually impacted by experimental noise to a higher degree than its hot-wire counterpart. The influence of noise on turbulence intensity statistics has been studied previously by drawing comparisons between PIV datasets and hotwire/DNS datasets to determine the noise floor for PIV measurements [CITATION_1] . Following a similar approach, we selected the smallest separation r to compute structure functions such that it was above the noise floor for each PIV measurement. Here the cutoff was chosen based on a direct comparison with a hot-wire dataset at a comparable Reynolds number.",
